<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto p-6">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Accessibility Guidelines</h1>
  
  <p class="mb-6">
    The Maybe UI component library is designed with accessibility in mind, following WCAG 2.1 AA standards to ensure all users can effectively use the application regardless of abilities.
  </p>
  
  <div class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Core Principles</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div class="border rounded-lg p-4 [data-theme=dark]:border-gray-700">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-2">Perceivable</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5">
          <li>Sufficient color contrast (4.5:1 minimum)</li>
          <li>Text alternatives for non-text content</li>
          <li>Content adaptable and distinguishable</li>
          <li>Multiple ways to access content</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="border rounded-lg p-4 [data-theme=dark]:border-gray-700">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-2">Operable</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5">
          <li>Keyboard accessible functionality</li>
          <li>Sufficient time to read and use content</li>
          <li>No content that causes seizures</li>
          <li>Navigable content structure</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="border rounded-lg p-4 [data-theme=dark]:border-gray-700">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-2">Understandable</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5">
          <li>Readable and predictable content</li>
          <li>Consistent navigation and identification</li>
          <li>Input assistance and error prevention</li>
          <li>Clear instructions and feedback</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="border rounded-lg p-4 [data-theme=dark]:border-gray-700">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-2">Robust</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5">
          <li>Compatible with current and future tools</li>
          <li>Valid HTML and ARIA usage</li>
          <li>Semantic markup structure</li>
          <li>Assistive technology support</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Component-Specific Guidelines</h2>
    
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="border rounded-lg p-4 [data-theme=dark]:border-gray-700">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-2">Interactive Elements</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5">
          <li><strong>Focus indicators:</strong> Visible focus states for all interactive elements</li>
          <li><strong>Touch targets:</strong> Minimum size of 44x44px for touch interactions</li>
          <li><strong>Keyboard operation:</strong> All functionality available via keyboard</li>
          <li><strong>ARIA roles:</strong> Proper roles for custom interactive elements</li>
          <li><strong>State management:</strong> ARIA states for current status (expanded, selected, etc.)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="border rounded-lg p-4 [data-theme=dark]:border-gray-700">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-2">Form Components</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5">
          <li><strong>Labels:</strong> All form controls have associated labels</li>
          <li><strong>Error states:</strong> Clear error messages with instructions</li>
          <li><strong>Required fields:</strong> Clearly indicated with both visual and programmatic markers</li>
          <li><strong>Input assistance:</strong> Help text and validation feedback</li>
          <li><strong>Grouping:</strong> Related controls are properly grouped</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="border rounded-lg p-4 [data-theme=dark]:border-gray-700">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-2">Modal Dialogs</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5">
          <li><strong>Focus management:</strong> Focus trapped within modal when open</li>
          <li><strong>Keyboard dismissal:</strong> ESC key closes the modal</li>
          <li><strong>ARIA attributes:</strong> role="dialog" and aria-modal="true"</li>
          <li><strong>Return focus:</strong> Focus returns to triggering element when closed</li>
          <li><strong>Screen reader announcements:</strong> Modal opening is announced</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="border rounded-lg p-4 [data-theme=dark]:border-gray-700">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-2">Content and Typography</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5">
          <li><strong>Heading hierarchy:</strong> Proper heading levels (h1-h6)</li>
          <li><strong>Text contrast:</strong> Minimum 4.5:1 ratio for normal text, 3:1 for large text</li>
          <li><strong>Text resizing:</strong> Content readable when zoomed to 200%</li>
          <li><strong>Line spacing:</strong> Adequate spacing for readability</li>
          <li><strong>Font size:</strong> Minimum 16px for body text</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Testing Accessibility</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">All components should be tested for accessibility using:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Keyboard navigation:</strong> Test tab order, focus states, and keyboard operation</li>
      <li><strong>Screen readers:</strong> Test with VoiceOver (macOS) and NVDA (Windows)</li>
      <li><strong>Color contrast:</strong> Verify using contrast checkers in both themes</li>
      <li><strong>Zoom:</strong> Test at 200% zoom level</li>
      <li><strong>Reduced motion:</strong> Test with prefers-reduced-motion media query</li>
      <li><strong>Automated tools:</strong> Use axe or similar tools for basic compliance checks</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  
